## Or use Lightning LoRA

You can also use lightning LoRA with your favortie sdxl model by activating the LoRA node here and using the 4-step lightning LoRA from here:

https://huggingface.co/ByteDance/SDXL-Lightning/tree/main

nodes.title: Video Input
widgets_values:
## Video Input Here you will be declaring the size of the video you want to upscale to, not the original size of the video.
I recommend having select-every_nth to be set at 2. It cuts down on the frames that will be processed and smooths the video. We then set FiLM VFI to 2 in this work flow to bring the frames back up.
Pay attention to the fps. For example, if your original video is 16 fps and you skip every 2rd, we're dropping the frames to 8fps. You'll want to then adjust the FiLM interpolator to multiply by 2 and set the video combine for 16 fps to get back to your original length.
If you're running out of CUDA Memory, you may need to split longer videos into 30 second clips or go for a smaller aspect ratio.
If your input video is a higher resolution, you will defintely have a harder time running this. I've been using videos that are 432x768 for upscaling.

nodes.title: Note+ (mtb)
widgets_values:
## Denoising

A Lower Denoise will result in something much closer to your original video. If the amount of added detail is too extreme for you, dial it down and see how that blends.

nodes.title: Note+ (mtb)
widgets_values:
## Interpolating and FPS

Make sure you bring the framerate back up to your original fps with FiLM and setting the proper fps in Video Combine.
